Text.Value: *Meow.*
Good things come to those who are forthcoming - but only if they make it count.
He dresses fabulously but stinks of the Hells - something infernal, to be sure. Abhorrent.

EditorData.NodeContext: Clear she does NOT like this person

Text.Value: You're a pretty kitty, aren't you?
Do I want to know about who's through those fancy curtains?
Your paws are fit to overturn only the daintiest crystalware.
But they do say a burden shared is a burden halved...

EditorData.NodeContext: Meaningfully - she wants to gossip with the player

Text.Value: *Hiss!*
Reach out to pet the cat.
Leave.
That's rather a broad topic - we get all sorts here. But there is one frequent visitor whose very presence offends me.
Of course, they are siblings - but judging from the throngs of clients they draw, most of the city is as disgusting as they are.
Then perhaps you would like to go and do them. Get thee hence.
Ah, you are quite correct - I consider them one of my finest features.
Sometimes a lady has to make her presence known - delicately, of course.
Come to pay your respects to the real lady of the house, I see. What a clever creature you are!

EditorData.NodeContext: Regal; like royalty greeting a subject

Text.Value: Leave.
Can't you hear from here? They're talking about the new top cat in the criminal underbelly - go and listen for yourself.

EditorData.NodeContext: Seemingly disappointed the player doesn't have cat hearing

Text.Value: What's that shady pair over there whispering about?
As for them personally: one never washes and instead douses himself with rose oil, while the other can't hold his drink.
Try and pet the cat.
Why should I?
It's your lucky day. I am receiving compliments at this time, and you are most welcome to make an offering.

EditorData.NodeContext: As if this is a great privilege

Text.Value: Unhand me, you ham-fisted oaf! You should know better than to touch unasked. Begone!
Ugh - no, thank you. So uncouth.
My favourite ungainly animal!
The drow - two of our most popular courtesans. A night with them seems to be rather life changing - if you can afford it.
Oh, you flatterer! But you are of course correct. My tail is quite the marvel.
I've got better things to do than compliment a cat.
The unwashed rabble who frequent this establishment have much to learn from your deference. And I must suffer their foibles alone.
Your glorious tail can trip an unsuspecting servant with the grace of an empress.
Leave.
Your eyes are two baleful jewels that strike fear into the most complacent of rats.
What are your thoughts on the clientele as a whole?
*Meow!*
*Meoooow. Purr.*

Synopsis: Dialog for the Mamzell Amira's cat. "The mascot of Sharess' Caress, a longhair ragdoll, She gazes at you with half-lidded eyes but keeps her opinion to herself. "
